  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BMZ - Lebanon Second top up (the Beirut blast)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the project is: to address the needs emerged as a result of the Beirut blast and identified during the rapid needs assessment and build on the experience of HelpAge and the partner organisations in Lebanon. It aims at providing basic relief health and protection services to older people directly or indirectly affected by the blast to help them cope with the emergency situation, while contributing to their resilience.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project supports older people affected by the Beirut blast through the provision of appropriate homebased medical and nursing care, psychological support services, and distribution of hygiene and elderly kits to households with older people identified in need</narrative>
  </description>
